<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-38-0948 </DOCNO><TEXT>The aim of this report is to review the experiment of Rose and Jones (discoveryin 1984 of radioactive decay of /sup 223/Ra by /sup 14/C nuclei emission)with the subsequent one of Alexandrov (et al) performed with the sametechnique. The experiments performed by the group at Orsay on /sup 14/Cradioactivity of radium isotopes with the magnetic spectrometer Solenoare also reviewed. This review comprises the presentation and commentsof the original results and arguments taken in their historical context.</TEXT></DOC>